01Blog

A modern social blogging platform for students to share knowledge, connect, and grow together.

🌐 Overview

01Blog is a fullstack social blogging platform designed for students to document their learning journey, share posts, interact with others, and build a learning community.

Users can:

Publish learning posts (text + media)
Follow other students
Like & comment on posts
Report inappropriate content
Receive notifications

Admins manage the platform through a powerful moderation dashboard.

🚀 Tech Stack
🖥 Backend
Java 17+
Spring Boot
Spring Security (JWT)
Spring Data JPA
PostgreSQL / MySQL
🎨 Frontend
Angular
Angular Material
TypeScript
RxJS
🛠 Tools
Maven
Node.js
Git & GitHub
✨ Features
🔐 Authentication & Security
User registration & login
JWT-based authentication
Role-based access control (USER / ADMIN)
Secure endpoints with Spring Security
Password encryption (BCrypt)
👤 User System
Public user profiles (“Blocks”)
Follow / unfollow users
View user activity & posts
Subscription-based feed system
📝 Posts System
Create / edit / delete posts
Support for images & videos
Post timestamps & previews
Like system ❤️
Comment system 💬
🔔 Notifications
Notifications for:
New posts from followed users
Likes & comments
Mark as read/unread
Notification center UI
🚨 Reporting System

Users can report:

Posts
User profiles

Each report includes:

Reason (required)
Timestamp (auto-generated)

Reports are:

Stored securely in database
Visible only to admins
Used for moderation actions
🛡️ Admin Panel

Admin can:

View all users
Manage posts (delete / hide)
Review reports
Ban / unblock users
Moderate platform content

All admin routes are protected by role-based authorization.

🎨 Frontend Features
Responsive UI (Angular Material / Bootstrap)
Home feed (subscribed users posts)
User profile pages
Post creation with media preview
Report modal with confirmation dialog
Admin dashboard interface
Clean and modern UX
🗄️ Database Design

Core entities:

Users
Posts
Comments
Likes
Subscriptions
Reports
Notifications
🔐 Security Architecture
JWT authentication flow
Secure route guards (frontend)
Role-based access control (backend)
Protected admin endpoints
Input validation on both sides
